  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "D1voJd4DbDDxvs8M5kfqVg3vyJs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Initial-state transfer pattern\n\nA participant who accepts an invitation needs the current state, not just future ops. Rather than inventing a new snapshot protocol, the design **reuses the existing document-share bundle**:\n\n- The invitation message carries a `shareReference` plus `actHistoryAddress` pointing to a one-shot drive bundle built via `buildDriveShareBundle`.\n- On accept, the recipient imports the bundle. Drive, folders, and docs materialize locally with the original signatures preserved.\n- After import, the recipient's SwarmChannel registers the peer feeds and starts pulling incremental ops.\n\nThis keeps the **snapshot path and the incremental-ops path decoupled**. The snapshot path is the same battle-tested import flow used by one-off document sharing; collab adds only the peer-feed subscription on top.\n\nBecause `action.context.signer.signatures` is preserved through imports (per the 2026-04-17 fix), the imported history already shows correct per-author attribution. New ops arriving through peer feeds continue the same signed chain.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
